parsed_answers.1: The SI unit of force is Newton (N). Definition: Newton is the force that produces an acceleration of 1 m/s² in a body of mass 1 kg. 1N = 1 kg m/s²
parsed_answers.2: Newton's third law states that for every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction.
parsed_answers.3: Speed is the rate of change of distance (a scalar quantity). Velocity is the rate of change of displacement.
